brands.description: The Print Shop is a basic desktop publishing software package developed in the early 1980s by Brøderbund. It was unique in that it provided libraries of clip-art and templates through a simple interface to build signs, posters and banners with household dot-matrix printers. Over the years the software has been updated to accommodate changing file formats and printer technologies.

transcript.text: With the release of One Print Shop version 12.1, we're excited to introduce a new product type, Dye Kit Personalization.

This feature is specifically designed for sticker products, allowing customers to create highly customized dye kit stickers with unique effects and personalization options that enhance both visual appeal and user engagement.
On the front door, users can upload or browse an image and apply various image operations that help them visualize their final product in real time.

The available operations include displaying the original image, removing the background for a clean cut out, cutting out the face for portrait face style stickers, and even applying A caricature effect to transform the image into a fun, cartoonish version.
Additionally, customers can preview special printing effects like gold, silver, or holographic finishes by selecting material options.
These effects can be further customized by adjusting border colors and widths, rotating or flipping the image to achieve the desired look from the admin panel.
Setting up a Die Kit Personalization product as simple and efficient.
Begin by creating a new product and selecting the Die Kit Personalization type.
This product supports only size based pricing.
Next, navigate to the Options tab and create a new option called Effects, assigning attribute values like gold, silver, and so on.
Once these options are defined, move to the Studio Events tab to bind each attribute to its respective event, such as assigning Silver to the Material type event with the attribute Silver.
Repeat this process for other materials or effect that you want to support.

With this configuration in place, you'll be able to offer customers a highly interactive and creative way to design personalized stickers while maintaining control over pricing and production parameters.
This new feature not only enhances the product catalog, but also opens new possibilities for customer engagement and premium offerings.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
